--><xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns="http://www.openapplications.org/oagis/10" targetNamespace="http://www.openapplications.org/oagis/10" elementFormDefault="qualified" attributeFormDefault="unqualified">
	<xsd:include schemaLocation="../Nouns/PaymentStatus.xsd"/>
	<xsd:element name="NotifyPaymentStatus" type="NotifyPaymentStatusType" id="oagis-id-4cd8ab87b09b4f32b8910dd5a068bbb4">
		<xsd:annotation>
			<xsd:documentation source="http://www.openapplications.org/oagis/10">The purpose of the NotifyPaymentStatus is to enable an application to request specific PaymentStatus information to be Notifyed by another business application module.

This typically a transaction that occurs between a company and a Bank in order to remit PaymentStatus to company that has provided goods or services.  

The response to the NotifyPaymentStatus is the AcknowledgePaymentStatus.</xsd:documentation>
		</xsd:annotation>
	</xsd:element>
	<xsd:complexType name="NotifyPaymentStatusType" id="oagis-id-50aea1b1ae2f43d19141e7525c0b7dfe">
		<xsd:complexContent>
			<xsd:extension base="BusinessObjectDocumentType">
				<xsd:sequence>
					<xsd:element name="DataArea" type="NotifyPaymentStatusDataAreaType" id="oagis-id-9944b109111e4ddbb016f64cad5da164">
						<xsd:annotation>
							<xsd:documentation source="http://www.openapplications.org/oagis/10">Is where the information that the BOD message carries is provided, in this case NotifyPaymentStatus. The information consists of a Verb and one or more Nouns. The verb (Notify) indicates the action to be performed on the Noun (PaymentStatus).</xsd:documentation>
						</xsd:annotation>
					</xsd:element>
				</xsd:sequence>
			</xsd:extension>
		</xsd:complexContent>
	</xsd:complexType>
	<xsd:complexType name="NotifyPaymentStatusDataAreaType" id="oagis-id-7359947b46674b05a236808369448081">
		<xsd:sequence>
			<xsd:element ref="Notify" id="oagis-id-f30f142df5cc42e8936eba48830be3a6"/>
